Rocket Design team members work on level one certification rocket projects at the Missouri S&T Student Design center. These projects are individual rockets built by a student they then fly for Tripoli level one rocket certification. Senior experienced team members demonstrate and train newer members through the projects to train and involve newer members in rocketry. When members successfully complete level one, they can move forward to level 2 and level three rocketry certifications. Nationally recognized certification is a requirement of several senior positions on the team. The most experienced and qualified members on the team need the higher level certifications to be permitted to launch the big rockets the team builds for competitions and clients. item.title: Events
item.dc:creator: ebc43
item.content:encoded:
You can use this page to list your upcoming meetings, competitions, and other events. You have several options for how to do this:

Link directly to the campus calendar (calendar.mst.edu)

If your team has a group on the campus calendar, it may be best to delete this page and instead place a Custom Link called Events in the same position in your menu under Appearance > Menu.

If you do not yet have a group on the campus calendar, contact websupport@mst.edu with the name of your design team and a list of members (names and emails) who can submit and manage your events. Please advise these members to log into the campus calendar first so that their accounts are created and can be added to your group.

While this option is potentially the simplest and most effective, its major drawback is that the campus calendar is only for events of interest to the wider campus community. A club's private meetings would not be appropriate for the main campus calendar. See the next option for a variation on this strategy that will allow both event types.

Embed the campus calendar for public events, use another calendar for private events

If your team has a group on the campus calendar, you can create an embeddable widget of events specific to your group to use on this site. Visit https://calendar.mst.edu/help/widget, filter events by your group, and select a layout. We recommend Widget Type: List and Style: Card. Retrieve the embed code and paste it into a Custom HTML block on this page.

If you do not yet have a group on the campus calendar, contact websupport@mst.edu with the name of your design team and a list of members (names and emails) who can submit and manage your events. Please advise these members to log into the campus calendar first so that their accounts are created and can be added to your group.

By embedding your public events, you can then make a heading below for your private events and embed another calendar of your choice there. You can activate Calendar+ under your Plugins menu to manage your events here in WordPress, or you can paste an embed code into a Custom HTML block from any other service (e.g. Google calendar).

Use the Calendar+ plugin

Your site is equipped with a plugin called Calendar+ that you can activate under the Plugins menu. This will allow you to manage events in WordPress like you would manage posts. Once some events have been added, insert a calendar block onto this page to display them.

Embed a third-party calendar

If your team already manages events in a third-party calendar like Google calendar, you can embed it using a Custom HTML block on this page.

Sponsorship Information

Sustainable Engineering Design Team would like to thank all the sponsors, mentors, advisors and friends that have made this design team a reality. If you are interested in donating, please follow the instructions below. Thank you so much for our support!

1 - In Person

To send a check, make it out to Missouri S&T with Sustainable Engineering on the memo line

Sustainable Engineering Design Team
c/o Tohajie Raet
1051 N Bishop Ave
116 Kummer Student Design Center
Rolla, MO 65409

2 - Online

To make a donation online, please click the button below​ and select "Designations". Under the Student Design & Experiential Learning Category, select Sustainable Engineering.

Donate Now

Sponsorship Levels

Blossom Buddy.

A donation above $5000. Blossom Buddies receive all previous benefits as well as:

  • Logo At ALL Events
  • Logo on all merchandise from the team

Petal Patron

A donation between $3000 and $4999. Petal Patrons receive all previous benefits as well as:

  • Logo on projects

Sprout Sponsor

A donation between $2000 and $2999. Sprout Sponsors receive all previous benefits as well as:

  • Logo at seminars

Seedling Supporter

A donation from $1000 and $1999. Seedling Supporter benefits include:

  • Shoutout on social media
  • Logo on website
  • Logo at our workshops

Dynamic Startup-like Environment, Hands-on Entrepreneurship and Engineering

Entrepreneurial

Our team members network, develop sponsor relationships, maintain a budget, compose business and legal documents, procure grants, and collaborate with the University and other Enactus organizations. Members of SUS-E develop the experience needed to build their own businesses in the future.

Interdisciplinary

We are a truly diverse team of majors and skills. Both STEM and non-STEM students work together for a common goal

Enactus Competition

We are a part of an international organization known as Enactus (Entrepreneurial, Action, Us), which holds annual business competitions. Each year we develop a new business idea for the competition, and old projects are maintained.

item.title: Competition
item.dc:creator: ajc3xc
item.content:encoded:
Enactus Competition

What is Enactus?

Enactus (Entrepreneurial Action Us) is a network of leaders committed to using business as a catalyst for positive social and environmental impact. Enactus educates, inspires, and supports young people to use innovation and entrepreneurship to solve the world's biggest problems.

Enactus Global
Enactus USA

Sustainable Development Goals

Enactus is committed to the 17 UN Sustainable Developmental Goals to have a better and more sustainable world by 2030. As an international organization, Enactus enables progress through Entrepreneurial Action and is aligned with the SDG goals, to improve people’s lives in communities, empowering them with values in a
sustainable way.

Annual Competition

Enactus Teams develop ideas into actual business solutions, which then are held at annual Enactus competitions.

Enactus Competitions are held annually at the National Exposition and Global Cup levels. Some countries hold Regional Expositions to narrow down the applicants for the National Exposition.

Enactus Teams present a 12 minute presentation to show their project and their impact, followed by a 5 minute Q&A by the judges. The judges score the presentation based on the Team Evaluation Form, and then rank them based on the Cumulative Evaluation Form. Winners then proceed to the next level in the competition or win the World Cup.
